---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Programmatic Remnant Banner Inventory for Ad Networks | AdBunny"
  description="Access aggregated remnant banner inventory programmatically. AI-optimized placement, real-time performance data, no manual tuning required."
  keywords="programmatic banner inventory access, remnant inventory for advertisers, ad network demand partner, real-time bidding banner ads"
>

<section class="pt-28 pb-12 max-md:pt-20">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="max-w-[44rem]">
      <h1 class="font-extrabold leading-[1.05] tracking-tight mb-4" style="font-size:clamp(2.25rem,5vw,3.5rem)">Programmatic access to aggregated remnant banner inventory</h1>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8 max-w-[34rem]" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny gives ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers efficient access to remnant banner inventory across our publisher network — with AI-driven placement optimization and real-time performance reporting.</p>
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-20 max-md:py-14" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-4">The scale problem with remnant inventory</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Remnant inventory is valuable, but it's fragmented across thousands of individual publishers, each with different setups, fill patterns, and placement quality. Accessing it efficiently — and optimizing performance across it — doesn't scale with manual processes.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 max-md:py-14">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-10">How AdBunny solves it</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">01</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Aggregated access</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Reach remnant banner inventory across the AdBunny publisher network through a single integration, instead of negotiating site by site.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">02</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">AI-optimized placement</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">AdBunny's optimization layer continuously improves banner performance across placements without requiring manual tuning on your end.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-3" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">03</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold tracking-tight mb-2">Real-time reporting</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Get placement-level performance data as it happens, so you can evaluate spend efficiency and adjust strategy with current information, not lagging reports.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-20 max-md:py-14" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="max-w-[40rem]">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
      <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Ad networks, DSPs, and media buyers looking to deploy banner campaigns efficiently against remnant inventory at scale, with data to back up performance decisions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-20 max-md:py-14 text-center">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">Get efficient access to remnant banner demand</h2>
    <p class="text-base mb-8" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Talk to our team about integrating with the AdBunny network.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary">Talk to Our Demand Team</a>
  </div>
</section>
</BaseLayout>
